2026-05-13          v0.2.0

                    Journal fallback: events that OpenSearch refused
                    after retries, or rejected at the per-item level,
                    are re-emitted on stderr as warn-level tracing
                    lines prefixed `logpipe-fallback` so systemd ships
                    them to the unit's journal instead of dropping
                    them silently.

                    Performance: _bulk request bodies are now gzip-
                    compressed (Content-Encoding: gzip) and built
                    once per batch as bytes::Bytes, so retries no
                    longer memcpy the (potentially multi-MB) payload.

                    Config: new optional batch.channel_capacity knob
                    controls the in-process queue depth between the
                    FIFO reader and the flusher. Default raised from
                    max_events * 2 (min 1024) to max_events * 8 so a
                    single slow flush no longer immediately backpres-
                    sures customer writers via the kernel pipe.


2026-05-12          v0.1.0

                    Initial version.